  "text": "The Kubernetes scheduler plugin framework is organized across 6 key files: (1) **interface.go** defines all plugin interfaces (Plugin, FilterPlugin, ScorePlugin, BindPlugin, PreFilterPlugin, PostFilterPlugin, PreScorePlugin, ReservePlugin, PermitPlugin, PreBindPlugin, PostBindPlugin, EnqueueExtensions) and the top-level Framework interface. (2) **schedule_one.go** contains `ScheduleOne` (the full scheduling workflow for a single pod) and `schedulePod` (the core scheduling algorithm). (3) **scheduler.go** defines the `Scheduler` struct and its `Run` method which starts the scheduling loop. (4) **runtime/framework.go** has the `frameworkImpl` struct that implements the Framework interface, including `RunFilterPlugins`, `RunFilterPluginsWithNominatedPods`, and `RunScorePlugins`. (5) **plugins/registry.go** contains `NewInTreeRegistry` which registers all built-in scheduler plugins. (6) **runtime/registry.go** defines the `Registry` type (`map[string]PluginFactory`) used for plugin registration. The call chain flows: Scheduler.Run -> ScheduleOne -> schedulePod -> frameworkImpl.RunFilterPlugins/RunScorePlugins.",
